50|$|Unlike other <b>magnetic</b> {{confinement}} <b>fusion</b> {{devices such}} as the tokamak, FRCs provide a magnetic field topology whereby the axial field inside the reactor is reversed by eddy currents in the plasma, {{as compared to the}} ambient magnetic field externally applied by solenoids. The FRC is less prone to magnetohydrodynamic and plasma instabilities than other <b>magnetic</b> confinement <b>fusion</b> methods. The science behind the colliding beam fusion reactor is used in TAE's C-2, C-2U and C-2W projects.|$|R
